{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mandate standardised Trans HRT pescribing training for all NHS GPs",
        "additional_details": "We feel this underserves the TNBI (Trans, Non Binary and Intersex) community. Ideally a letter from a NHS GIC or NHS Gender Service to pescribe and what dosages should be sufficient.\r\n\r\nWe are asking that the Government mandate TNBI pescribing training to all NHS GPs on a national level to so a TNBI person can access HRT pescribing at any NHS GP, anywhere within the whole of the country, without all the uncertainty.",
        "background": "Many NHS GPs will not offer shared care for hormone pescribing for Trans patients who are under the care of a NHS GIC (Gender Identity clinic). In many cases, many of them cite not having training, or adequate training to do so.",
